Modern MVC


View ---------------------> Controller ---------------------> Model ---------------------> Controller --------------------->  View
     ( user input, event )         ( modify upon business logic )  ( pulls vis getters & setters )    (represents state on the ui)


01. Model
Contains the app state ( Data, Logic, State that user wants to see & manipulate )
No business logic in the model

02. Controller
Interprets user interaction with the view into action that modifies the model

03. View
Visualize app state according to model & allow user to interact with it.

